        "System.Description": "<div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><br><span style=\"display:inline !important;\">Vsoft scan check dialog shows debit and credit as 0.00 when there are items with values are scanned and submitted. EJ&nbsp;<span style=\"display:inline !important;\">View does not populate scan check dialog with virtual tickets and scanned items.&nbsp;</span></span></div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><br style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"></div></div><div><br></div><div>1- Add Scan Bond Button in GL Credit transaction for adjustment during day 2 process\n<br></div>2.This scans the bond image but processes as a check, so it will not recalculate the Redemption value and will not generate a 1099 report.\n<br>3-This requires VSoft provides a Bond mode 3 functionality which is scanning a Bond as a check.\n<br><br>There is a Vsoft part to this enhancement request as well. \n<br><br>This will be a denorm and .dll fix. <hr>Reporter: Mohammed Mohiuddin<hr>External ID: 1912<hr>Components: <hr>Affiliates affected: NBA,NSB,VBC,ZFNB,ABT,CBT<hr>Original assignee: Trung Thai<hr>Found with a Test Case",
        "Microsoft.VSTS.TCM.SystemInfo": "<div>Zeus Teller&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Miscellaneous -&gt; GL Credit Transaction</div><div>Teller Functions -&gt; EJ View</div>",
        "Microsoft.VSTS.TCM.ReproSteps": "<div>1- Launch GL Credit Tranasaction</div><div>2- Select GL account from drop down and enter serial number</div><div>3- Click scan bond button</div><div>4- Scan bonds in the Vsoft scan bond dialog and observe the debits and credits</div><div><br></div><div>Result: The debit and credit show 0.00.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>5- Complete the transaction and View in EJ</div><div><br></div><div>Result: EJ View does not populate scan check dialog with virtual ticket and scanned items.&nbsp;</div>",
        "System.Tags": "ALL AFFILIATES; ZEUS-8081"
    },
